quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  36,49,"They do not await except one blast{1} which will seize them while they are disputing.",footnotes:1:Literally, "cry" or "shriek," meaning the first blast of the Horn which will strike dead every living thing on the earth without warning.
  36,50,"And they will not be able [to give] any instruction, nor to their people can they return."
  36,51,"And the Horn will be blown;{1} and at once from the graves to their Lord they will hasten.",footnotes:1:For the second time, signaling the Resurrection.
  37,34,"Indeed, that is how We deal with the criminals."
  37,35,"Indeed they, when it was said to them, "
  37,36,"And were saying, "
  38,13,"And [the tribe of] Thamūd and the people of Lot and the companions of the thicket [i.e., people of Madyan]. Those are the companies.{1}",footnotes:1:That were defeated, among whom will be the disbelievers of Quraysh and others.
  38,14,"Each of them denied the messengers, so My penalty was justified."
  38,15,"And these [disbelievers] await not but one blast [of the Horn]; for it there will be no delay.{1}",footnotes:1:Or "respite."  More literally, "a period between two milkings of a she-camel," which also alludes to the meanings of "return" or "repetition."